<h1>@HI{{tame ni}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<p>
<ol>
<li>@Vru{{}}(<em>volitional</em>) <strong>@HI{{tame ni}}</strong>, <em>volitional expression</em>
<li>@N{{}} @HI{{no}} <strong>@HI{{tame ni}}</strong>
</ol>
</p>

<h2> Definition </h2>

These sentence patterns indicate a purpose. The pattern @N{{}} @HI{{no tame ni}} can also indicate
"for the benefit of @N{{}}".
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<h2> Notes </h2>

The similar expression @HI{{you ni}} is used in clauses with verbs that do not contain volition,
whereas @HI{{tame ni}} is used with verbs that do.
